Reasoning: The paper discusses the application of AI techniques, specifically stochastic dynamic programming, to address decision making under uncertainty in public health. This falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a Markov decision process also suggests relevance to control systems (cs.SY) and optimization (cs.CE). Finally, the focus on health policy design and development suggests potential relevance to social and information sciences (cs.SI).
